Then, using `noHo_of_minimal_expert_sequence`, we get that for this minimal $m$, any sequence $\sigma$ of length less than $2m-4$ that makes all $m$ agents experts must satisfy `noHo σ`, meaning no agent hears their own secret in $\sigma$.

However, for $n \geq 4$, any sequence that makes all agents experts must contain at least $n-1$ calls where each call is between two agents. But in such a sequence, some agent must hear their own secret, contradicting `noHo σ`.

